In the coming years, climate change could force hundreds of millions of people to flee their homes. Those in the poorest regions of the world will be the most affected. Governments should be planning in advance for these mass migrations. This film looks at why this is not happening, and at how this looming crisis should be managed better. Right now the focus of most governments in the rich world is on measures which eliminate emissions, such as investing in renewable energy, and on adaptive actions, such as building flood defences. But they should also be putting resources into how and where to move affected people. 